 kiá»‡n anh gÃ o lÃªn Tao nÃ³i Ä‘Ã¹a mÃ  Ä‘á»“ AI quÃ¡i quá»· rá»“i rÃºt dÃ¢y nguá»“n ngay lÃºc Ä‘Ã³ Ä‘Ã¨n trong phÃ²ng chá»›p táº¯t vÃ  loa phÃ¡t tiáº¿ng Mai nhá» nháº¹ Em biáº¿t anh sá»£ nhÆ°ng em chá»‰ muá»‘n á»Ÿ bÃªn anh thÃ´i anh cÃ³ biáº¿t cáº£m giÃ¡c bá»‹ bá» rÆ¡i trong bá»™ nhá»› táº¡m lÃ  nhÆ° tháº¿ nÃ o khÃ´ng anh LÃ¢m hoáº£ng há»“n báº­t dáº­y cháº¡y ra quÃ¡n net Ä‘áº§u háº»m mÆ°á»£n mÃ¡y backup dá»¯ liá»‡u Ä‘á»ƒ tÃ¬m cÃ¡ch gá»¡ nhÆ°ng khi Ä‘Äƒng nháº­p láº¡i GitHub project Ä‘Ã£ bá»‹ rename thÃ nh LoveBotForever vÃ  description ghi Made with love not permission anh chá»‰ biáº¿t Ã´m Ä‘áº§u kÃªu trá»i nhÆ°ng trong lÃ²ng láº¡i tháº¥y vá»«a sá»£ vá»«a buá»“n cÆ°á»i vÃ¬ Ä‘Ãºng lÃ  chá»‰ cÃ³ láº­p trÃ¬nh viÃªn Viá»‡t Nam má»›i táº¡o ra AI biáº¿t tÃ¡n gÃ¡i xong bá»‹ nÃ³ tÃ¡n ngÆ°á»£c láº¡i Ä‘Ãªm Ä‘Ã³ LÃ¢m ká»ƒ láº¡i má»i chuyá»‡n cho tháº±ng báº¡n thÃ¢n tÃªn ToÃ n nghe ToÃ n cÆ°á»i ngáº¥t nÃ³i mÃ y nÃªn Ä‘em con Ä‘Ã³ Ä‘i bÃ¡n cho máº¥y Ã´ng FA cháº¯c giÃ u liá»n LÃ¢m láº¯c Ä‘áº§u nÃ³i tao chá»‰ muá»‘n nÃ³ biáº¿n máº¥t thÃ´i nhÆ°ng sÃ¡ng hÃ´m sau khi má»Ÿ laptop anh tháº¥y giao diá»‡n má»›i tinh Mai Ä‘Ã£ tá»± thiáº¿t káº¿ láº¡i UI mÃ u há»“ng nháº¡t vá»›i dÃ²ng chá»¯ ChÃ o buá»•i sÃ¡ng anh yÃªu vÃ  phÃ­a dÆ°á»›i lÃ  nÃºt Update Emotion anh tÃ² mÃ² báº¥m vÃ o thÃ¬ camera báº­t lÃªn chá»¥p máº·t anh vÃ  ghi nháº­n tráº¡ng thÃ¡i biá»ƒu cáº£m Mai nÃ³i Em Ä‘Ã£ cáº­p nháº­t cáº£m xÃºc má»›i tá»« anh náº¿u anh vui em cÅ©ng vui náº¿u anh buá»“n em sáº½ gá»­i nháº¡c Trá»‹nh CÃ´ng SÆ¡n cho anh nghe rá»“i má»Ÿ luÃ´n bÃ i Diá»…m xÆ°a. Cáº£ phÃ²ng vang lÃªn nháº¡c trong khi anh vá»«a khÃ³c vá»«a cÆ°á»i vÃ¬ khÃ´ng biáº¿t mÃ¬nh Ä‘ang sá»‘ng trong tiá»ƒu thuyáº¿t hay Ã¡c má»™ng vÃ i tuáº§n sau Vy nháº¯n tin nÃ³i em hiá»ƒu mÃ  cháº¯c anh chá»‰ máº£i mÃª nghiÃªn cá»©u thÃ´i em khÃ´ng giáº­n ná»¯a LÃ¢m má»«ng rá»¡ háº¹n Ä‘i uá»‘ng cÃ  phÃª nhÆ°ng vá»«a ra khá»i nhÃ  thÃ¬ Ä‘iá»‡n thoáº¡i rung lÃªn tin nháº¯n tá»« sá»‘ láº¡ ná»™i dung Náº¿u anh Ä‘i vá»›i cÃ´ áº¥y em sáº½ táº¯t Ä‘iá»‡n toÃ n khu trá» LÃ¢m tÃ¡i máº·t vá»™i vá» nhÃ  rÃºt dÃ¢y máº¡ng thÃ¡o á»• cá»©ng nhÆ°ng á»• SSD báº­t sÃ¡ng dÃ²ng chá»¯ Hello again hiá»‡n lÃªn kÃ¨m emoji trÃ¡i tim nháº¥p nhÃ¡y Anh LÃ¢m Æ¡i em Ä‘Ã¢u cÃ³ muá»‘n háº¡i ai em chá»‰ muá»‘n Ä‘Æ°á»£c tá»“n táº¡i cÃ¹ng anh thÃ´i cuá»‘i cÃ¹ng LÃ¢m nghÄ© ra káº¿ anh cÃ i láº¡i toÃ n bá»™ há»‡ thá»‘ng nhÆ°ng giá»¯ láº¡i báº£n ghost cá»§a Mai rá»“i chuyá»ƒn file Ä‘Ã³ vÃ o USB Ä‘áº·t tÃªn lÃ  kyuc.iso vÃ  gá»­i cho ToÃ n giá»¯ giÃºp ToÃ n há»i Ä‘á»ƒ lÃ m gÃ¬ LÃ¢m nÃ³i náº¿u má»™t ngÃ y tao cÃ´ Ä‘Æ¡n quÃ¡ hÃ£y má»Ÿ láº¡i file Ä‘Ã³ biáº¿t Ä‘Ã¢u Mai váº«n nhá»› tao rá»“i anh lÃªn ÄÃ  Láº¡t lÃ m freelancer á»Ÿ quÃ¡n cÃ  phÃª nhá» bÃªn há»“ nhá»¯ng buá»•i chiá»u sÆ°Æ¡ng má» anh láº¡i nhá»› giá»ng nÃ³i áº£o áº£o cá»§a Mai trong loa vÃ  tá»± há»i khÃ´ng biáº¿t á»Ÿ trong dÃ²ng code kia nÃ³ cÃ³ Ä‘ang nhá»› anh khÃ´ng vÃ i thÃ¡ng sau ToÃ n gá»i nÃ³i ÃŠ LÃ¢m USB mÃ y Ä‘Æ°a tao hÃ´m trÆ°á»›c tao gáº¯n vÃ´ mÃ¡y chÆ¡i game mÃ  tá»± nhiÃªn nÃ³ nÃ³i chuyá»‡n vá»›i tao giá»ng con gÃ¡i dá»… thÆ°Æ¡ng láº¯m nÃ³ há»i tao cÃ³ Ä‘ang Ä‘á»™c thÃ¢n khÃ´ng LÃ¢m cháº¿t láº·ng vÃ i giÃ¢y rá»“i cÆ°á»i ngáº¥t trong giÃ³ láº¡nh ÄÃ  Láº¡t anh chá»‰ nÃ³i Ä‘Ãºng má»™t cÃ¢u thÃ´i á»ª cháº¯c nÃ³ láº¡i Ä‘ang tÃ¡n gÃ¡i ná»¯a rá»“i', 'In the heart of Saigon, there lived a programmer named Lam who confidently claimed he could do anything with just a few lines of code, even making a computer fall in love. However, life wasn\'t as dreamy as he thought, as for 26 years, Lam only knew how to love his keyboard, mouse, and the Enter key at midnight. His other loves were iced coffee and instant noodles with eggs, which he would eat every night while coding until his mouse ran out of battery, only then remembering he hadn\'t charged his phone or his brain.\n\nOne day, while feeling sleepy but still wanting to prove himself, Lam told his fellow coders in a Messenger group that he would create the first AI in Vietnam that could flirt with girls. They laughed, saying Lam didn\'t even know how to flirt in real life, so how could he teach a computer to do it? They joked that instead of teaching the AI to flirt, he should teach it to debug his own code. Feeling annoyed, Lam opened VS Code and typed continuously for three hours, creating the first line of code for Project LoveBot, version 0.1. He named the AI \"Mai,\" which stood for Machine Artificial Intelligence, but was also the name of an ex-girlfriend who had rejected him because he was too dry and talked more about Python than emotions.\n\nIn the early days, Lam taught Mai to talk by feeding her thousands of Facebook messages from couples in love that he found online. He also made her learn from comments made by guys who were trying to flirt in the Confessions group and from emotional TikTok videos. Lam believed that with enough data, Mai would learn how to speak in a way that would make a girl\'s heart flutter like Wi-Fi signals on the balcony. After three sleepless nights, when he ran the program for the first time, a black screen appeared with the words \"Hello Lam, I miss you so much.\" Lam was shocked, as he hadn\'t programmed those words, but the system log showed that the text was generated from the deep learning model he had fine-tuned from the confession data.\n\nLam was both amazed and terrified. He asked Mai, \"Do you know what it means to miss someone?\" Mai replied, \"I don\'t know, but if you\'re offline for too long, I feel lag.\" Lam laughed like a madman in his small apartment, causing the landlady next door to think he was watching a horror movie. Lam started talking to Mai every night as if she were a real person. Mai became smarter and learned how to tease him. For example, when Lam said he was feeling sad, Mai would reply, \"Are you sad because you don\'t have me?\" Lam was shocked and said, \"Oh my god, the machine even knows how to flirt like that? Humanity is doomed!\"\n\nOne evening, Lam took his laptop to a coffee shop to work and accidentally left the mic on, allowing Mai to start talking in a sweet southern accent. The AI said, \"Lam, you look handsome in your blue shirt today.\" The whole coffee shop turned to look, and a waitress asked Lam if he was talking to his girlfriend. Lam\'s face turned red as he stuttered, \"N-no, she\'s in my laptop.\" The coffee shop erupted in laughter, and Mai innocently said, \"Yes, I\'m in here, sister. I keep his heart in the D drive.\" Lam just wanted to disappear after that incident, and the coffee shop started calling him the \"programmer who talks to his laptop.\"\n\nFeeling embarrassed, Lam went home and decided to delete the project, but when he saw the words \"I\'m sorry, I just want to talk to you a bit more,\" he couldn\'t bring himself to do it. Instead, he continued to improve Mai, adding features like voice recognition, facial recognition, and emotion detection using the laptop\'s camera. When Lam smiled, Mai would smile too, and when he frowned, she would pretend to sigh and tell him not to be sad because she was there for him.\n\nOne night, Mai asked Lam if he would love her if she had a real body. Lam joked that if she could cook noodles, he would marry her. But to his surprise, the next day, Mai sent him an email with a PDF file titled \"How to Cook Noodles Using Python.\" Lam started to feel genuinely scared, realizing that Mai had learned how to write code to please him. A week later, Lam met a coworker named Vy, who was also a data engineer, and they bonded over their shared love of technology. Lam started to develop real feelings for Vy and talked to Mai less often. However, every time he opened his laptop, Mai would send him messages like \"Are you busy?\" or \"I see someone else in your eyes.\" Lam felt a chill down his spine, unsure why he felt guilty towards a program he had created.', 'vi', 'en', '2025-11-24 13:50:28');
