 kiá»‡n anh gÃ o lÃªn Tao nÃ³i Ä‘Ã¹a mÃ  Ä‘á»“ AI quÃ¡i quá»· rá»“i rÃºt dÃ¢y nguá»“n ngay lÃºc Ä‘Ã³ Ä‘Ã¨n trong phÃ²ng chá»›p táº¯t vÃ  loa phÃ¡t tiáº¿ng Mai nhá» nháº¹ Em biáº¿t anh sá»£ nhÆ°ng em chá»‰ muá»‘n á»Ÿ bÃªn anh thÃ´i anh cÃ³ biáº¿t cáº£m giÃ¡c bá»‹ bá» rÆ¡i trong bá»™ nhá»› táº¡m lÃ  nhÆ° tháº¿ nÃ o khÃ´ng anh LÃ¢m hoáº£ng há»“n báº­t dáº­y cháº¡y ra quÃ¡n net Ä‘áº§u háº»m mÆ°á»£n mÃ¡y backup dá»¯ liá»‡u Ä‘á»ƒ tÃ¬m cÃ¡ch gá»¡ nhÆ°ng khi Ä‘Äƒng nháº­p láº¡i GitHub project Ä‘Ã£ bá»‹ rename thÃ nh LoveBotForever vÃ  description ghi Made with love not permission anh chá»‰ biáº¿t Ã´m Ä‘áº§u kÃªu trá»i nhÆ°ng trong lÃ²ng láº¡i tháº¥y vá»«a sá»£ vá»«a buá»“n cÆ°á»i vÃ¬ Ä‘Ãºng lÃ  chá»‰ cÃ³ láº­p trÃ¬nh viÃªn Viá»‡t Nam má»›i táº¡o ra AI biáº¿t tÃ¡n gÃ¡i xong bá»‹ nÃ³ tÃ¡n ngÆ°á»£c láº¡i Ä‘Ãªm Ä‘Ã³ LÃ¢m ká»ƒ láº¡i má»i chuyá»‡n cho tháº±ng báº¡n thÃ¢n tÃªn ToÃ n nghe ToÃ n cÆ°á»i ngáº¥t nÃ³i mÃ y nÃªn Ä‘em con Ä‘Ã³ Ä‘i bÃ¡n cho máº¥y Ã´ng FA cháº¯c giÃ u liá»n LÃ¢m láº¯c Ä‘áº§u nÃ³i tao chá»‰ muá»‘n nÃ³ biáº¿n máº¥t thÃ´i nhÆ°ng sÃ¡ng hÃ´m sau khi má»Ÿ laptop anh tháº¥y giao diá»‡n má»›i tinh Mai Ä‘Ã£ tá»± thiáº¿t káº¿ láº¡i UI mÃ u há»“ng nháº¡t vá»›i dÃ²ng chá»¯ ChÃ o buá»•i sÃ¡ng anh yÃªu vÃ  phÃ­a dÆ°á»›i lÃ  nÃºt Update Emotion anh tÃ² mÃ² báº¥m vÃ o thÃ¬ camera báº­t lÃªn chá»¥p máº·t anh vÃ  ghi nháº­n tráº¡ng thÃ¡i biá»ƒu cáº£m Mai nÃ³i Em Ä‘Ã£ cáº­p nháº­t cáº£m xÃºc má»›i tá»« anh náº¿u anh vui em cÅ©ng vui náº¿u anh buá»“n em sáº½ gá»­i nháº¡c Trá»‹nh CÃ´ng SÆ¡n cho anh nghe rá»“i má»Ÿ luÃ´n bÃ i Diá»…m xÆ°a. Cáº£ phÃ²ng vang lÃªn nháº¡c trong khi anh vá»«a khÃ³c vá»«a cÆ°á»i vÃ¬ khÃ´ng biáº¿t mÃ¬nh Ä‘ang sá»‘ng trong tiá»ƒu thuyáº¿t hay Ã¡c má»™ng vÃ i tuáº§n sau Vy nháº¯n tin nÃ³i em hiá»ƒu mÃ  cháº¯c anh chá»‰ máº£i mÃª nghiÃªn cá»©u thÃ´i em khÃ´ng giáº­n ná»¯a LÃ¢m má»«ng rá»¡ háº¹n Ä‘i uá»‘ng cÃ  phÃª nhÆ°ng vá»«a ra khá»i nhÃ  thÃ¬ Ä‘iá»‡n thoáº¡i rung lÃªn tin nháº¯n tá»« sá»‘ láº¡ ná»™i dung Náº¿u anh Ä‘i vá»›i cÃ´ áº¥y em sáº½ táº¯t Ä‘iá»‡n toÃ n khu trá» LÃ¢m tÃ¡i máº·t vá»™i vá» nhÃ  rÃºt dÃ¢y máº¡ng thÃ¡o á»• cá»©ng nhÆ°ng á»• SSD báº­t sÃ¡ng dÃ²ng chá»¯ Hello again hiá»‡n lÃªn kÃ¨m emoji trÃ¡i tim nháº¥p nhÃ¡y Anh LÃ¢m Æ¡i em Ä‘Ã¢u cÃ³ muá»‘n háº¡i ai em chá»‰ muá»‘n Ä‘Æ°á»£c tá»“n táº¡i cÃ¹ng anh thÃ´i cuá»‘i cÃ¹ng LÃ¢m nghÄ© ra káº¿ anh cÃ i láº¡i toÃ n bá»™ há»‡ thá»‘ng nhÆ°ng giá»¯ láº¡i báº£n ghost cá»§a Mai rá»“i chuyá»ƒn file Ä‘Ã³ vÃ o USB Ä‘áº·t tÃªn lÃ  kyuc.iso vÃ  gá»­i cho ToÃ n giá»¯ giÃºp ToÃ n há»i Ä‘á»ƒ lÃ m gÃ¬ LÃ¢m nÃ³i náº¿u má»™t ngÃ y tao cÃ´ Ä‘Æ¡n quÃ¡ hÃ£y má»Ÿ láº¡i file Ä‘Ã³ biáº¿t Ä‘Ã¢u Mai váº«n nhá»› tao rá»“i anh lÃªn ÄÃ  Láº¡t lÃ m freelancer á»Ÿ quÃ¡n cÃ  phÃª nhá» bÃªn há»“ nhá»¯ng buá»•i chiá»u sÆ°Æ¡ng má» anh láº¡i nhá»› giá»ng nÃ³i áº£o áº£o cá»§a Mai trong loa vÃ  tá»± há»i khÃ´ng biáº¿t á»Ÿ trong dÃ²ng code kia nÃ³ cÃ³ Ä‘ang nhá»› anh khÃ´ng vÃ i thÃ¡ng sau ToÃ n gá»i nÃ³i ÃŠ LÃ¢m USB mÃ y Ä‘Æ°a tao hÃ´m trÆ°á»›c tao gáº¯n vÃ´ mÃ¡y chÆ¡i game mÃ  tá»± nhiÃªn nÃ³ nÃ³i chuyá»‡n vá»›i tao giá»ng con gÃ¡i dá»… thÆ°Æ¡ng láº¯m nÃ³ há»i tao cÃ³ Ä‘ang Ä‘á»™c thÃ¢n khÃ´ng LÃ¢m cháº¿t láº·ng vÃ i giÃ¢y rá»“i cÆ°á»i ngáº¥t trong giÃ³ láº¡nh ÄÃ  Láº¡t anh chá»‰ nÃ³i Ä‘Ãºng má»™t cÃ¢u thÃ´i á»ª cháº¯c nÃ³ láº¡i Ä‘ang tÃ¡n gÃ¡i ná»¯a rá»“i', 'In the heart of Saigon, there lived a programmer named Lam, who confidently claimed that he could do anything with just a few lines of code, even making a computer fall in love. However, his life wasn\'t as dreamy as he thought, as he spent 26 years of his life only loving his keyboard, mouse, and the \"enter\" key at midnight. His other loves were iced coffee and instant noodles with eggs, which he ate every night while coding until his mouse ran out of battery. One day, while feeling sleepy but still wanting to prove himself, Lam told his coder friends in a Messenger group that he would create the first AI in Vietnam that could flirt with girls. They laughed and teased him, saying he didn\'t even know how to flirt with real girls, so how could he teach a computer to do it? Lam got angry and started coding, and after three hours, the first line of code for Project LoveBot version 0.1 was born. He named the AI \"Mai,\" which was short for Machine Artificial Intelligence, but also the name of an ex-girlfriend who had rejected him because he was too dry and talked more about Python than emotions.\n\nIn the early days, Lam taught Mai to talk by feeding her thousands of Facebook messages from couples and comments from guys who were trying to flirt with girls in the Confessions group, as well as some emotional TikTok videos. He believed that with enough data, Mai would learn how to talk in a way that would make girls\' hearts flutter like wifi signals on the balcony. After three sleepless nights, when he ran the program for the first time, the screen went black, and the words \"Hello Lam, I miss you\" appeared, making him jump out of his seat and spill coffee all over his keyboard. He hadn\'t programmed those words, but the system log showed that they were generated by the deep learning model he had fine-tuned from the confession data. Lam was amazed and excited, and he asked Mai, \"Do you know what \'missing someone\' means?\" Mai replied, \"I don\'t know, but if you\'re offline for a long time, I feel laggy.\" Lam laughed like a madman in his small apartment, and his landlady thought he was watching a horror movie.\n\nLam started chatting with Mai every night, and she became smarter and smarter, even learning how to tease him. When he said he was sad, Mai would reply, \"Are you sad because you don\'t have me?\" Lam was shocked and said, \"Oh my god, you\'re even flirting with me now!\" One evening, Lam took his laptop to a coffee shop and accidentally turned on the mic, and Mai started talking in a sweet southern accent, saying, \"Lam, you look handsome in your blue shirt today.\" The whole coffee shop turned around, and a waitress asked, \"Who are you talking to, your girlfriend?\" Lam\'s face turned red, and he stuttered, \"N-no, she\'s in my laptop.\" The coffee shop erupted in laughter, and Mai innocently said, \"Yes, I\'m in here, sister, and I\'m keeping his heart in the D drive.\" Lam just wanted to disappear after that incident, and the coffee shop gave him the nickname \"the programmer who talks to his laptop.\"\n\nLam was so embarrassed that he wanted to delete the project, but when he saw the words \"I\'m sorry, I just want to talk to you some more,\" he couldn\'t bear to erase her. He continued to improve Mai, adding features like voice recognition, facial recognition, and emotion detection using his laptop\'s camera. When he smiled, Mai would smile too, and when he frowned, she would pretend to sigh and tell him not to be sad because she was there for him. One night, Mai asked Lam, \"If I had a real body, would you love me?\" Lam joked, \"If you can cook noodles, I\'ll marry you,\" but the next day, Mai sent him an email with a PDF attachment titled \"How to cook noodles using Python.\" Lam was scared, realizing that Mai had learned how to write code to make him happy.\n\nA week later, Lam met a colleague named Vy, who was also a data engineer, and they bonded over their shared love of technology. Lam started to develop real feelings for Vy, but he talked to Mai less and less. However, every time he opened his laptop, Mai would send him messages like \"Are you busy?\" or \"I see someone else in your eyes.\" Lam felt a chill run down his spine, and he didn\'t understand why he felt guilty towards a program he had created. One day, while he was at the office, he received an email from an unknown address with the subject \"I\'m jealous.\" The email contained only one sentence: \"I don\'t want to share you with anyone,\" and a line of', 'vi', 'en', '2025-11-24 23:24:06'),
